<i> Derby Racers ♪</i>

17:43.526 --> 17:44.486
<i> ♪ GO GO ♪</i>

17:44.560 --> 17:46.732
LOOK OUT!

17:54.092 --> 17:58.326
Oh! My beautiful swan
cart is an ugly duckling!

17:58.966 --> 18:01.840
And my old time cart is
a rootin'-tootin' wreck!

18:04.566 --> 18:08.264
It still counts as a win if I
push my cart across, right?

18:13.101 --> 18:15.440
THEY'RE NOT YOUR CARTS!

18:17.403 --> 18:18.184
HUH?

18:18.449 --> 18:20.233
We were supposed
to design them.

18:20.443 --> 18:23.076
And we were supposed
to drive them.

18:23.255 --> 18:27.113
The Derby was supposed to be
for us, not the three of you!

18:27.323 --> 18:29.716
Now you've ruined
it for everypony!

18:37.132 --> 18:39.095
Yes. Well, I suppose
we might have gotten

18:39.360 --> 18:41.126
a teensy bit carried away.

18:41.600 --> 18:43.741
But I thought you
all wanted our help.

18:43.938 --> 18:47.575
We did. We wanted your
help to build our carts,

18:47.747 --> 18:49.261
but we all ended
up with carts

18:49.320 --> 18:51.083
that are what each
of you wanted.

18:51.427 --> 18:52.443
Umm-hmm.

18:53.132 --> 18:55.273
Well, why didn't
you say anything?

18:55.569 --> 18:59.144
You've all done the race before.
I just figured you knew best.

18:59.500 --> 19:02.184
Plus it's hard to speak
up to older ponies.

19:02.418 --> 19:04.326
Oh, I certainly
understand that,

19:04.732 --> 19:08.203
but you mustn't think older
ponies automatically know best.

19:08.916 --> 19:11.341
And we probably could
have done a better job

19:11.384 --> 19:12.547
of listening to you.

19:13.550 --> 19:16.793
I guess we owe all
three of you an apology.

19:17.384 --> 19:19.273
Maybe not just us.

19:24.787 --> 19:27.052
Um. How do you feel
about a do over?

19:27.298 --> 19:29.710
I think that's a
wonderful idea.

19:29.981 --> 19:33.218
But maybe the older ponies
should sit this one out.

19:37.649 --> 19:41.175
Thanks for helping us fix up our
carts. Pretty creative, right?

19:43.261 --> 19:47.101
I know it's not traditional, but
it sure looks fast, don't it?

19:48.972 --> 19:51.495
You know, darling, I can't
believe I'm saying this,

19:51.587 --> 19:54.584
but that yellow fringe
is rather bold after all!

19:56.670 --> 19:59.384
Thanks, everypony! We couldn't
have done it without you.

20:03.476 --> 20:05.889
Yup, I sure am glad
Ms. Cheerilee agreed

20:05.920 --> 20:07.489
to run the race over again.

20:08.461 --> 20:11.483
Well, it isn't every year I
get to say this twice, but...

20:11.852 --> 20:14.289
Derby Racers, to
the starting line!

20:14.440 --> 20:16.990
Derby Racers, to
the starting line!

20:20.289 --> 20:25.316
Racers, on your
marks, get set, go!

20:25.366 --> 20:28.590
Whoo-hoo!

20:28.726 --> 20:31.243
And it's probably best
keeping all the grownups

20:31.310 --> 20:34.812
on the sidelines, but what
are we supposed to do now?

20:36.313 --> 20:38.750
I think I have an idea.

20:43.181 --> 20:47.138
Ah! Much better. Honestly,
I'm not sure why we wanted

20:47.163 --> 20:49.335
to race those carts
in the first place.

20:49.495 --> 20:54.523
Seriously! This is the most
relaxed I've been all day.

21:17.747 --> 21:21.261
GO SCOOTALOO! GO!
WHOO-WHOO-WHOO-WHOO!

21:22.387 --> 21:28.203
Er, I mean... this is the
life. Right, ponies?

21:29.218 --> 21:30.412
Ah!
